cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about using a convolutional neural network for prostate segmentation in MRI images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of loss functions for training the network, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of residual connections, which are commonly used in deep learning architectures, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with volumetric segmentation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
